                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5001: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prince</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-25T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Your 40 of August 24. There is absolutely no basis for semiofficial reports
                    that we are seeking to apply Hoover Plan to Yugoslavia despite its
                    non-acceptance. The American Government has taken no steps to influence any of
                    the interested parties.</p>
                <p>While we do not wish to be in a position of advising Yugoslavia it would appear
                    natural that the Yugoslav Government should endeavor to solve its difficulties
                    through the B. I. S.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
